\section{Module state}

We need a handful of global variables to coordinate between
initialisation (at import time) and cleanup (at exit time).
The [[repo]] variable also serves as an initialisation guard: if it is
not [[None]], we have already initialised and should not do so again.
This handles the case where multiple files in the same program all
\mintinline{python}{import learnlog}.

<<module state>>=
repo = None
iolog = None
original_stdout = None
original_stderr = None
original_stdin = None
exception_info = None
start_time = None
main_script = None
main_args = None
@


\section{Finding the learnlog directory}

Before creating a new repository, we search upward from the current
directory for an existing [[.learnlog/]] directory, mirroring how Git
itself searches for [[.git/]].
This lets a student work across multiple lab subdirectories while all
activity is recorded in a single repository at the course root.
The function lives in the core module because both import-time
initialisation and the CLI need it.

<<functions>>=
def find_learnlog_dir(start=None):
    """Walk up from ``start`` to find a ``.learnlog/`` directory.

    Returns the directory containing ``.learnlog/``, or ``None``
    if no learnlog repository is found.
    """
    path = pathlib.Path(start or os.getcwd()).resolve()
    while True:
        if (path / ".learnlog").is_dir():
            return path
        parent = path.parent
        if parent == path:
            return None
        path = parent
@

Let's verify that the upward search works correctly.
These tests use [[LearnlogRepo]] (\cref{gitrepo}) to create a
[[.learnlog/]] directory in an isolated temporary directory:

<<test functions>>=
class TestFindLearnlogDir:
    def test_find_in_current(self, workdir):
        """find_learnlog_dir returns the directory
        containing .learnlog/."""
        from learnlog import find_learnlog_dir
        LearnlogRepo(workdir)
        assert find_learnlog_dir(workdir) == workdir

    def test_find_from_subdirectory(self, workdir):
        """find_learnlog_dir walks up to find
        .learnlog/ in a parent."""
        from learnlog import find_learnlog_dir
        LearnlogRepo(workdir)
        sub = workdir / "subdir"
        sub.mkdir()
        assert find_learnlog_dir(sub) == workdir

    def test_returns_none_when_missing(self, tmp_path):
        """find_learnlog_dir returns None if no
        .learnlog/ exists."""
        from learnlog import find_learnlog_dir
        assert find_learnlog_dir(tmp_path) is None
